# Git Push Policy

After committing changes to the repository, always push to GitHub unless the user explicitly says otherwise (e.g., "don't push" or "commit only").

When making edits to the codebase:
1. Stage and commit changes with a clear message
2. Push to the remote (typically `origin main`) unless told not to
